A word of advice, if the criticism seems immature or not serious, why take it seriously? Anybody can say “this sucks”. It’s the people who say why it sucks that you should listen to.
I know somebody may say “you don’t need to know how to write to know bad writing” kinda like how everybody knows if a car is shit yet they can’t build a car, but in general people can tell in certain terms why something is bad. Most people may not know all the terminology used for whatever they criticize, but if they try to make a point and make it understandable, try to understand it.
I know this all seems obvious but common sense is sadly not that common.
